JPMorgan Chase Bank, National Association Key Developments

Himax Technologies, Inc. Appoints JPMorgan Chase Bank, N.A. as New American Depository Receipt Bank
Jul 19 17
Himax Technologies Inc. announced its appointment of JPMorgan Chase Bank, N.A. as the Company’s American Depository Receipt (ADR) bank. Effective July 19, 2017, Himax’s ADR program is officially transferred to JPMorgan Chase Bank, N.A.


JPMorgan Chase Bank, National Association Reports Audited Consolidated Financial Results for the Year Ended December 31, 2016
Mar 15 17
JPMorgan Chase Bank, National Association reported audited consolidated financial results for the year ended December 31, 2016. For the year, the company reported interest income of USD 41,584 million against USD 37,425 million for the same period of last year. Net interest income was USD 36,942 million against USD 33,689 million for the same period of last year. Total net revenue was USD 78,186 million against USD 73,380 million for the same period of last year. Net income was USD 19,372 million against USD 16,928 million for the same period of last year. Net cash provided by operating activities was USD 37,545 million against USD 48,069 million for the same period of last year.


Mahindra & Mahindra Limited Appoints J.P Morgan Chase Bank N.A as Overseas Depositary
Jan 4 17
Mahindra & Mahindra Limited appointed J.P morgan chase bank N. A as its overseas depositary for managing the global depository receipt program of the company with effect from January 3, 2017 in place of the bank of New York, Mellon.


